So The problem is in the sorting algorithm.&lt;br&gt; 
Merge Sort&#39;s time Complexity is *Nlog(N)* And all you have added is one single line
&gt;             inv_count = inv_count + (mid - i);

 of constant complexity So it won&#39;t change the overall complexity of your algorithm. There won&#39;t be any problem in counting the number of inversions in the array even if the inputs are *100000*.&lt;br&gt;

